# MCP Resources

Resources are application-controlled data sources that MCP servers expose to provide context to AI applications. They represent things like files, database schemas, API responses, and configuration — any data that enriches the LLM's understanding.

## Resource Definition

Each resource has:
- **`uri`** — Unique identifier using standard URI schemes (file://, https://, custom://)
- **`name`** — Human-readable name
- **`title`** — Optional display name
- **`description`** — What the resource contains
- **`mimeType`** — Content type (text/plain, application/json, etc.)
- **`size`** — Optional size in bytes
- **`annotations`** — Optional metadata (audience, priority, lastModified)

## Python (FastMCP)

```python
from mcp.server.fastmcp import FastMCP

mcp = FastMCP("resources-example")

@mcp.resource("file://readme")
def readme() -> str:
    """Project README file."""
    return open("README.md").read()

@mcp.resource("schema://database")
def db_schema() -> str:
    """Database schema definition."""
    return open("schema.sql").read()

@mcp.resource("config://app")
def app_config() -> str:
    """Application configuration."""
    return json.dumps(load_config(), indent=2)
```

## TypeScript (McpServer)

```typescript
import { McpServer } from "@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/mcp.js";

const server = new McpServer({ name: "resources-example", version: "1.0.0" });

server.resource(
  "readme",
  "file://readme",
  async (uri) => ({
    contents: [{
      uri: uri.href,
      mimeType: "text/markdown",
      text: await fs.readFile("README.md", "utf-8")
    }]
  })
);
```

## Protocol Messages

### List Resources: `resources/list`

```json
// Request
{"jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 1, "method": "resources/list"}

// Response
{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 1,
  "result": {
    "resources": [{
      "uri": "file:///project/README.md",
      "name": "README.md",
      "description": "Project documentation",
      "mimeType": "text/markdown"
    }]
  }
}
```

### Read Resource: `resources/read`

```json
// Request
{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 2,
  "method": "resources/read",
  "params": {"uri": "file:///project/README.md"}
}

// Response
{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 2,
  "result": {
    "contents": [{
      "uri": "file:///project/README.md",
      "mimeType": "text/markdown",
      "text": "# My Project\n\nA great project."
    }]
  }
}
```

### Resource Templates

Templates allow parameterized resource URIs using RFC 6570 URI templates:

```json
// resources/templates/list response
{
  "resourceTemplates": [{
    "uriTemplate": "file:///{path}",
    "name": "Project Files",
    "description": "Access files in the project directory",
    "mimeType": "application/octet-stream"
  }]
}
```

### Subscriptions

Clients can subscribe to resource changes:

```json
// Subscribe
{"jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 3, "method": "resources/subscribe", "params": {"uri": "file:///config.json"}}

// Server notification when resource changes
{"jsonrpc": "2.0", "method": "notifications/resources/updated", "params": {"uri": "file:///config.json"}}
```

## Content Types

### Text Content
```json
{"uri": "file:///example.txt", "mimeType": "text/plain", "text": "Content here"}
```

### Binary Content
```json
{"uri": "file:///image.png", "mimeType": "image/png", "blob": "base64-encoded-data"}
```

## Common URI Schemes

| Scheme | Use Case |
|--------|----------|
| `file://` | Filesystem-like resources |
| `https://` | Web-accessible resources (client can fetch directly) |
| `git://` | Git version control resources |
| Custom | Application-specific schemes (e.g., `db://`, `config://`) |

## Annotations

```json
{
  "uri": "file:///README.md",
  "name": "README",
  "annotations": {
    "audience": ["user", "assistant"],
    "priority": 0.8,
    "lastModified": "2025-01-12T15:00:58Z"
  }
}
```

## Error Handling

- Resource not found: JSON-RPC error code `-32002`
- Internal errors: JSON-RPC error code `-32603`
